                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d690">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.01/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-11T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 11, 1930—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>203. The Papal Nuncio has just informed me that the Holy See is recognizing the
                    junta today. The Nuncio stated that this action was intended to be a gesture of
                    good feeling toward the Peruvian people. Confidentially the Nuncio stated that
                    it was impossible for him satisfactorily to solve his multifarious problems with
                    the local authorities without recognition.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
